has the appearance of a spiny 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 549. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ammannii" order="Solanales" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ammannii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Convolvulus ammannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it is sometimes confused, but flowers sessile and clustered.
</paragraph>
